This is the first workshop in CIKM conference that addresses the challenge of large data management based on cloud computing infrastructure. This workshop will bring together researchers and practitioners in cloud computing and data-intensive system design, programming, parallel algorithms, data management, scientific applications, and information-based applications to maximize performance, minimize cost and improve the scale of their endeavors. Totally this workshop attracted 11 submissions from Asia, Canada, Europe, and the United States. The program committee accepted 8 papers, among which there are 5 full papers and 3 short papers. Topics of accepted papers includes query processing & index, service in the Cloud, platform availability, Cloud system implementation, data replication and so on. These proceedings will serve as a valuable reference for cloud data management researchers and developers.